# Vercel must ONLY build the Next.js dashboard in frontend/.
# The Python backend (main.py, api/, merger/, etc.) is deployed on Render, NOT Vercel.
# Without this, Vercel auto-detects root-level main.py + api/ and tries to run the
# FastAPI backend as a Python serverless function — which crashes every request with
# ModuleNotFoundError: No module named 'fastapi'.
#
# NOTE: The real fix is setting the Vercel project's Root Directory to `frontend`.
# This file is a safety net in case that setting is ever lost.
main.py
api/
merger/
eval/
sdk/
ageval/
examples/
tests/
requirements.txt
requirements-dev.txt
rate_limiter.py
*.py
